---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import ContactSection from "../components/ContactSection.astro";
import Button from "../components/Button.astro";
import Link from "../components/Link.astro";

const ticker = [
	"PHOTOGRAPHER",
	"DJ",
	"PROBLEM SOLVER",
	"FREELANCER",
	"MUSIC PRODUCER",
	"HUSBAND",
	"COFFEE GEEK",
	"HOUSE MUSIC ENJOYER",
	"GAME DEVELOPER",
];
---

<Layout title="Portfolio">
	<div>
		<!-- Hero -->
		<section class="min-h-[calc(100vh-3.5rem)] flex flex-col justify-between px-6 pt-16 pb-0 max-w-7xl mx-auto">
			<div style="animation: fade-up 0.6s ease-out both;">
				<h1
					class="text-foreground leading-none uppercase"
					style="font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif; font-weight: 900; font-size: clamp(4rem, 14vw, 12rem); letter-spacing: -0.02em;"
				>
					SOFTWARE
					<br />
					<span style="color: var(--primary);">DEVELOPER</span>
				</h1>

				<p
					class="text-muted-foreground uppercase"
					style="font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.5rem); letter-spacing: 0.04em; margin-top: 0.25em;"
				>
					AND...
				</p>

				<!-- Scrolling ticker -->
				<div class="mt-6 border-t border-border overflow-hidden py-4">
					<div
						class="flex gap-12 whitespace-nowrap"
						style="animation: ticker 30s linear infinite; width: max-content;"
					>
						{
							ticker.map((item, i) => (
								<span
									class="text-muted-foreground"
									style="font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.15em;"
								>
									{item}
									<span style="color: var(--primary); margin-left: 3rem;">—</span>
								</span>
							))
						}
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start justify-between gap-8 mt-12">
					<p
						class="text-muted-foreground max-w-md"
						style="font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.6;"
					>
						Six years building backend systems in fintech — Java, Spring Boot, AWS. I recently started doing
						freelance projects on the side, and they've made clear what I want more of: work where I own
						more of the picture and stay close to the people using it.
					</p>
					<div
						class="text-muted-foreground"
						style="font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em;"
					>
						BASED IN
						<br />
						<span class="text-foreground">CHICAGO, IL</span>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="pb-16"></div>
		</section>

		<!-- Projects CTA -->
		<section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6" style="animation: fade-up 0.5s ease-out 0.2s both;">
			<Button href="/projects" class="gap-4 px-8 py-5">
				<span
					style="font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.3rem; letter-spacing: 0.06em;"
				>
					VIEW ALL PROJECTS
				</span>
				<span style="font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.9rem;">→</span>
			</Button>
		</section>

		<!-- About / Other Interests -->
		<section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 mt-32">
			<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-16">
				<!-- About -->
				<div>
					<h2
						class="text-foreground uppercase mb-8 border-b border-border pb-4"
						style="font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.5rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em;"
					>
						ABOUT
					</h2>
					<div class="space-y-6">
						<div class="flex gap-6">
							<span
								class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0 mt-0.5"
								style="font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.7rem;">01</span
							>
							<p class="text-muted-foreground" style="font-size: 0.875rem; line-height: 1.6;">
								Based in Chicago since 2020, my professional background is backend engineering in
								fintech — Java, Spring Boot, lately a lot of AWS, REST APIs, data pipelines,
								integrations. Over the last year I've had more room to actually shape things: backend
								architecture for an analytics platform, ingestion pipeline design, cross-team planning
								for a client onboarding system. That kind of ownership is new for me, and it's been the
								most interesting work I've done yet.
							</p>
						</div>
						<div class="flex gap-6">
							<span
								class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0 mt-0.5"
								style="font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.7rem;">02</span
							>
							<p class="text-muted-foreground" style="font-size: 0.875rem; line-height: 1.6;">
								On the side I've been building for people I know — a site for a DJ collective's
								open-deck signups and events, a customizable portfolio for a DJ, my own wedding website.
								I got to see how real people use my work which matters a lot to me, and I want more of
								it. I'm open to full-time, freelance, or contract at any scale — what I care about is
								ownership and building things people actually use.
							</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<!-- Other interests -->
				<div>
					<h2
						class="text-foreground uppercase mb-8 border-b border-border pb-4"
						style="font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.5rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em;"
					>
						OUTSIDE WORK
					</h2>
					<div class="space-y-6">
						<div class="flex gap-6">
							<span
								class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0 mt-0.5"
								style="font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.7rem;">01</span
							>
							<p class="text-muted-foreground" style="font-size: 0.875rem; line-height: 1.6;">
								I just recently started releasing music last year. House music — jazzy, bouncy, jackin',
								dub, I have a lot of influences. If that sounds like your vibe, check out my project
								Grid District. <Link href="/music">MORE INFO</Link>
							</p>
						</div>
						<div class="flex gap-6">
							<span
								class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0 mt-0.5"
								style="font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.7rem;">02</span
							>
							<p class="text-muted-foreground" style="font-size: 0.875rem; line-height: 1.6;">
								I picked up DJing to get a bit closer to the local music scene. I've done a couple shows
								at a local bar and coffee shop, but it's mostly a way for me to vibe with friends and
								more actively listen to my favorite tunes.
							</p>
						</div>
						<div class="flex gap-6">
							<span
								class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0 mt-0.5"
								style="font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.7rem;">03</span
							>
							<p class="text-muted-foreground" style="font-size: 0.875rem; line-height: 1.6;">
								I enjoy photography and like to walk around documenting my surroundings, be it
								architecture, people, spaces, or landscapes. Beyond serving as a relaxing vehicle for
								getting out of the house, I've also covered some music shows and done portraits for
								friends.
							</p>
						</div>
						<div class="flex gap-6">
							<span
								class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0 mt-0.5"
								style="font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.7rem;">04</span
							>
							<p class="text-muted-foreground" style="font-size: 0.875rem; line-height: 1.6;">
								I got into biking a few years ago as a fun way to get some exercise in. I also enjoy
								tinkering and building up my 90's steel hybrid gravel conversion.
							</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<ContactSection />
	</div>
</Layout>
